  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support platform for formal and non-formal civil society groups in Lebanon and Syria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Lebanon, civil society is very dynamic with more than 5,000 associations registered with the Ministry of Interior. The weaknesses of the State in providing basic services to the population led to the emergence of NGOs trying to offset this absence or lack of services. Following the Syria crisis, new associations or non-formal groups, were established to provide basic support to Syrian refugees in Lebanon or in Syria.  Building on the experience of Mada following the war in 2006 when Mada was asked to provide support to non-formal groups in order to help them design and implement their projects (which led to the successful establishment of organisations such as Lebanon Support; and online research and information platform on public action and civil society issues), and recognising that services currently on offer by other INGOS are largely insufficiently tailored to smaller organisations to add real value, especially in relation to the needs of small organisations with limited financial and human resources, this project will support Mada in re-launching their platform for development in order to support NGOs or non-formal groups (both Syrian and Lebanese) to  achieve their mission and objectives without leading to a change in the spirit, values or characteristics of these organisations.  This project will target 4 organisations (2 Lebanese, 2 Syrian), although if the platform takes on additional beneficiaries with priority given to Syrian groups. It forms part of CAFOD&apos;s support to peace building work in Lebanon by facilitating collaboration between Lebanese and Syrian civil society groups, thereby contributing to increased social cohesion between these communities.  It will also support the development and strengthening of a strong and vibrant Syrian civil society able to contribute to peace building in Syria in the future.</narrative>
  </description>
